Patch: aurora lib/webgpu/gpu.cpp -- skip dawn::native::DawnInstanceDescriptor on MinGW-ABI compilers
Applies to: Aurora repo itself (external_refs/repos/aurora), commit 1dde08f.
Tracked file, edited directly (not a FetchContent dependency).

Why:
With AURORA_DAWN_PROVIDER=package (the Windows default -- see
cmake/AuroraDawnProvider.cmake), Dawn is consumed as encounter/dawn's
prebuilt `dawn-windows-amd64.tar.gz` release asset. That package is built
with the Microsoft C++ ABI (only one Windows/amd64 variant is published;
there is no MinGW-ABI counterpart -- checked via
`gh release view <tag> --repo encounter/dawn --json assets`).

aurora_core built and linked completely clean under zig cc
(x86_64-windows-gnu) *except* for one call site, `initialize()` in
lib/webgpu/gpu.cpp:

    #ifdef WEBGPU_DAWN
    dawn::native::DawnInstanceDescriptor dawnInstanceDescriptor;
    dawnInstanceDescriptor.backendValidationLevel = dawn::native::BackendValidationLevel::Disabled;
    dawnInstanceDescriptor.SetLoggingCallback(wgpu_log);
    ...
    instanceDescriptor.nextInChain = &dawnInstanceDescriptor;
    #endif

`dawn::native::DawnInstanceDescriptor` is Dawn's C++ "native" extension API
(dawn/native/DawnNative.h) -- a real C++ class compiled into
webgpu_dawn.dll/lib with MSVC name mangling and class layout. A MinGW-ABI
compiler (Itanium mangling/layout, incl. zig cc's x86_64-windows-gnu
target) cannot link against it. Confirmed by direct build attempt:

    lld-link: error: undefined symbol: dawn::native::DawnInstanceDescriptor::DawnInstanceDescriptor()
    >>> referenced by lib/webgpu/gpu.cpp:764
    >>>               libaurora_core.a(gpu.cpp.obj):(aurora::webgpu::initialize(AuroraBackend, bool))

This is the *only* dawn::native (C++ native-extension) usage anywhere in
Aurora's lib/ tree (grepped). Everywhere else, gpu.cpp uses Dawn's plain
`wgpu::`-namespaced C++ wrapper (webgpu_cpp.h), which is a header-only
inline forwarder to the `extern "C"` WebGPU C API (wgpuCreateInstance,
etc.) -- those symbols are undecorated/ABI-neutral at the x64 Windows
calling-convention level and link fine from either MSVC or MinGW-ABI code
against the same prebuilt DLL, as proven by the rest of aurora_core/gx
linking without any other undefined-symbol errors.

Fix: skip the whole dawn::native::DawnInstanceDescriptor block (and its
`#include <dawn/native/DawnNative.h>`) when `__MINGW32__` is defined. This
only loses Dawn's default backend-validation-level override and Aurora's
custom Dawn-internal logging-callback hookup (Tracy's dawn platform hookup
is unaffected either way -- it's already separately gated on
TRACY_ENABLE, which defaults OFF). wgpu::CreateInstance and everything
else in initialize() is untouched and still runs.

--- a/lib/webgpu/gpu.cpp
+++ b/lib/webgpu/gpu.cpp
@@ -21,7 +21,9 @@
 #ifdef WEBGPU_DAWN
 #include "../dawn/BackendBinding.hpp"
 #include "../dawn/TracyPlatform.hpp"
-#include <dawn/native/DawnNative.h>
+#ifndef __MINGW32__
+#include <dawn/native/DawnNative.h>
+#endif
 #endif

@@ -760,7 +762,16 @@ bool initialize(AuroraBackend auroraBackend, bool allowCpu) {
         wgpu::InstanceFeatureName::TimedWaitAny,
     };
     wgpu::InstanceDescriptor instanceDescriptor{...};
-#ifdef WEBGPU_DAWN
+#if defined(WEBGPU_DAWN) && !defined(__MINGW32__)
+    // dawn::native::DawnInstanceDescriptor is Dawn's C++ "native" extension API
+    // (dawn/native/DawnNative.h), compiled into the prebuilt webgpu_dawn.dll/lib
+    // with the Microsoft C++ ABI. A MinGW-ABI compiler (incl. zig cc's
+    // x86_64-windows-gnu target) mangles/lays out these C++ symbols differently
+    // and cannot link against them -- confirmed via direct build attempt
+    // (lld-link: undefined symbol dawn::native::DawnInstanceDescriptor::
+    // DawnInstanceDescriptor()). Skipping this block only loses Dawn's default
+    // backend-validation level override and Aurora's custom Dawn-internal
+    // logging callback hookup; wgpu::CreateInstance and the rest of the WebGPU
+    // C API below are extern "C" and link fine regardless of ABI.
     dawn::native::DawnInstanceDescriptor dawnInstanceDescriptor;
     dawnInstanceDescriptor.backendValidationLevel = dawn::native::BackendValidationLevel::Disabled;
     dawnInstanceDescriptor.SetLoggingCallback(wgpu_log);
@@ -771,3 +782,3 @@ bool initialize(AuroraBackend auroraBackend, bool allowCpu) {
     instanceDescriptor.nextInChain = &dawnInstanceDescriptor;
 #endif

Verified: after this change, `aurora_core`/`aurora_gx` and the `simple`
example link completely under zig cc (x86_64-windows-gnu) with
AURORA_DAWN_PROVIDER=package, and the resulting executable runs (see
0003-command-processor-unaligned-load-void-ptr.patch for the next --
separate -- issue this uncovered at runtime). MSVC builds are unaffected
(__MINGW32__ is never defined there), confirmed by rebuilding and rerunning
the build-msvc tree after this patch.
